commit.message: Some works to make glfw work on mingw

Uh, no.  Reverting the previous commit

It is far more easier to ask users to preinstall glfw packages.
pacman -Sy mingw-w64-x86_64-glfw mingw-w64-i686-glfw

Add conditionals for some extension support

OSX wants them.

Suppress warnings using GL on OSX

OSX deprecated OpenGL API and we get flood of warnings without
this definition.
Reflect argument order change of gl-draw-elements etc.

Change interface of gl-draw-elements etc. for the consistency

The C API takes mode, count, type, and pointer to index array.  If we give
an index array directly, we can deduce count and type from it, so
we don't need them.  If we use data in VBO, however, we need them;
previously we made count and type optional to handle those two cases,
but it made the latter call awkward, for the order of arguments
doesn't match C API.

We revised it so that it works polymorphically:
 (gl-draw-elements mode index-vec)  ; direct data
 (gl-draw-elements mode count type [offset]) ; use VBO

Same change for gl-draw-range-elements and gl-draw-elements-base-vertex.

NB: gl-vertex-pointer family has a similar issue, but in their case
we also need to support passing u8vector _AND_ type.  We'll think over.
Remove reference to ARB in the doc
More redbook examples and glext APIs
Allow gl-color-pointer etc to use VAOs
Start adding examples from the redbook 9th edition
Update glfw example with non *-arb API
Gl-vertex-attrib-pointer does not need pointer to the data
Fix bugs in perspective matrix calculation
Refactor CHECK_ERROR cise macro to glcase.scm
